* Annotation_01 6: @Inherited

➡ @Inherited is a marker annotation that can be used only on annotation declaration.

➡ @Inherited causes the annotation for a Parent class to be inherited by a child class.
  👉 Therefore, when a request for a specific annotation is made to the child class,
     if that annotation is not present in the child class, then its parent class is checked.

➡ If that annotation is present in the superclass, and if it is annotated with @Inherited,
  then that annotation will be returned.


